Micro-Macinazione S.A.

On 26 July 2017, Lonza completed the acquisition of Micro-Macinazione SA, a company specializing in the micronization of active ingredients for the pharmaceutical and ﬁne chemical industries, based in Molinazzo di Monteggio, (CH). The total cash consideration amounted to CHF 67 million,

The acquisition is reported within the Pharma&Bioteeh segment and does not have a significant impact on the consolidated financial statements for the twelve—month period ended 31 December 2017, with the exception of the acquired goodwill and intangible assets.

Impact from 2017 Acquisitions on Consolidated Income Statement

If the 2017 acquisitions had occurred on 1 J anuaxy 2017, Group sales in 2017 would have been CHF 5,660 million (+ CHF 555 million) and the Group result from operating activities CHF 783 million (+ CHF 60 million). These amounts were calculated using the Group’s accounting policies and by adjusting the results of the subsidiaries to reﬂect the full year amortization that would have been charged if the fair value adjustments to intangible assets had applied from January 2017.
